types.section:
{{fr-verb}}

# {{lb|fr|literally}} to [[like]] [[better]]
# to [[prefer]]
#: {{syn|fr|préférer}}
#: {{uxi|fr|J{{'}}'''aime mieux''' la campagne que la ville.|I '''prefer''' the country to the town.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|J{{'}}'''aimerais''' encore '''mieux''' ne plus jamais en parler.|I'd '''rather''' not talk about it ever again.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|N{{'}}'''aimeriez'''-vous pas '''mieux''' le voir par vous-même ?|Wouldn't you '''rather''' see it for yourself?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|J{{'}}'''aime''' bien '''mieux''' savoir que de croire.|I '''prefer''' knowing to believing.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Est-ce que tu '''aimerais mieux''' que je le fasse ?|Would you '''rather''' ''I'' did it?}}

====Usage notes====
* The comparative adverbial element {{m|fr|mieux}} can be rendered superlative ({{m|fr||aimer le mieux|t=to most prefer, i.e., to like best}}) or modified by certain intensifying adverbs: <ref name="tlfi"/>
*: {{m|fr||aimer bien mieux|t=to much prefer}}
*: {{m|fr||aimer encore mieux|t=to prefer even more}}
*: {{m|fr||aimer beaucoup mieux|t=to much prefer}}
*:: {{small|etc.}}
* If {{m|fr||aimer}} has a direct-object complement: <ref name="tlfi"/>
** no preposition or conjunction is needed to introduce a nominal or infinitive verbal complement;
** {{m|fr|que}} is used to introduce a complement consisting of a subjunctive verbal element or a prepositional locution.
* If {{m|fr||mieux}} has a complement of comparison, that complement can be marked in different ways depending on its contents: <ref name="tlfi"/>
** {{m|fr|que}} introduces a complement consisting of nominal or pronominal elements;
** {{m|fr|que de}} introduces a complement consisting of an infinitive verbal element
*** note that {{m|fr|de}} can optionally be omitted,<ref>{{R:Lbu14|page=1473|section={{abbr|§1131|Le mode dans la proposition corrélative}} c 2º}}</ref> however, this may slightly alter the meaning;<ref>{{R:Lbu14|page=1473|section=§1131 R2}}</ref>
** {{m|fr|que si}} can be used to introduce a complement consisting of a verbal element conjugated in personal form.
